contents.value: Attend WIC to sign up for pregnancy medicaid
MOB will attend visits as scheduled.
MOB is very busy and works nights, OS has encouraged.
Randy took off his diaper. MOB asked him to come to her to put one back on. Randy ran saying," No, no, no!"  MOB left him without a diaper.
Randy stayed close to his mother during the visit. MOB offered to hold him and he ran away. MOB was gentle in her touch.
MOB talked to Randy in a playful voice saying," Come here, let's put your diaper on." " Hey, diaper!" Randy would babble back to his mother.
MOB said that Randy will follow them to the bathroom and watches. She said he is not showing much interest at this time.

There was good back and forth interaction between MOB and child. MOB opened the fruit snacks and would hand them to Randy one at a time. Randy dropped one and MOB gave verbal directions to help him find it.
MOB showed joy at today's visit. MOB laughed and teased with Randy. MOB said," You are a chicken." Randy responded," I am not a chicken," and ran away.

We met at the family home. OS brought a book for the family. OS also brought plastic eggs and showed MOB how she could teach several basic concepts with them. MOB used to eggs to try and get Randy to tell her the colors. MOB had been to her last OB visit. She is considered high risk with birth spacing and high blood pressure with her last baby. MOB said she is starting to get excited about being pregnant, but is also worried. MOB's ultrasound had shown a subchorionic hematoma.  OS invited MOB to the next MDO. MOB said she will try to come. OS also gave MOB a handout about our upcoming Easter event at WKO.  Randy was playing when OS arrived. He had taken off his diaper and remained naked during the visit. MOB said he is not showing interest in being potty trained, but doesn't always like to wear his diaper. Randy's eczema is better on his legs. MOB has been using lotion. Randy is doing a lot of invented speech, but is also using some sentences. MOB can understand most of what he says. MOB said that Randy shares well with his little brother, but not with other children. He is holding his pencil correctly and likes to draw and color. MOB said she is glad it is getting nicer outside. Randy likes to play outside.
OS Jeanine DeLong
